    <name>
				<text>6.2.1.2 Separate odd and even parts</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise&nbsp;</p>
<p></p><p>Separate the function \(f(x) = {@fx@}\) into odd and even parts.</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li><p>First, find \(f(-x)\).</p><p>\(f(-x) = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>
<li><p>Next, find the even part of \(f(x)\): [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>
<li><p>Finally, find the odd part of \(f(x)\): [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p></li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We have the the function \(f(x) = {@fx@}.\)</p>
<p>\[ f(-x) = {@fnx@} \]</p>
<p>The even part is given by \[ \frac{1}{2}[f(x) + f(-x)] = {@even1@} = {@x^n+ 1/2*(a^x+a^(-x))@}. \]</p>
<p>The odd part is given by \[ \frac{1}{2}[f(x) - f(-x)] = {@odd1@} = {@1/2*(a^(-x)-a^x)@}. \]</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
    <defaultgrade>1.0000000</defaultgrade>
